Executive Profile
Robert J. Gillette  Chief Executive Officer and Director, ServiceMaster Global Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships57$5,859,985As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Robert J. Gillette, also known as Rob, has been the Chief Executive Officer of The ServiceMaster Company LLC  since June 17, 2013. Mr. Gillette has been the Chief Executive Officer of ServiceMaster Global Holdings, Inc. since June 17, 2013. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of First Solar Inc., from October 2009 to October 2011. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Honeywell Technology Solutions Inc. from January 2005 to September 2009. ... In this role, He managed Aerospace's three main business units, Aircraft Landing Systems, Aviation Electronics Services and Engines Systems and Services. He served as the President of Aerospace business of Honeywell International Inc. from January 7, 2005 to September 2009. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Transportation and Power Systems of Honeywell International Inc. from July 2001 to January 7, 2005. Mr. Gillette served as the President of Garrett Engine Boosting Systems from July 2000 to June 2001 and as Vice President and General Manager of Honeywell's Engineering Plastics business from December 1996 to June 2000. He served as the President of Honeywell Turbo Technologies and also served in the Turbo business as Vice President of Strategic Growth and Vice President/General Manager of Asia. He had leadership responsibility for Honeywell's three automotive-related businesses: Turbo Technologies, the Consumer Products Group, which consists of the Fram, Prestone and Autolite brands and Friction Materials, a major global supplier of automotive brake friction materials and aftermarket brake products. Before joining Honeywell in 1996, he had a decade of experience with General Electric Plastics in various positions with increasing responsibility in the United States and Europe in marketing and general management. During his tenure with GE, he also served as General Manager of South America. He has been a Director at ServiceMaster Global Holdings, Inc. since June 17, 2013. He served as a Director of First Solar, Inc., from October 2009 to October 2011. He served as a Member of Board of Governors at Aerospace Industries Association until January 2010. Mr. Gillette holds a Bachelor's of Science Degree in Finance from Indiana University.Read Full Background




